UNICEF-Sierra Leone COVID-19 Dashboard

Tracking health seeking behaviour, outcomes and government responses to COVID-19 in Sierra Leone

Continuous access to information on key economic indicators is essential to help Sierra Leone respond to the Covid-19 pandemic.dashboard provides real time data on current health trends from a phone based survey being rolled out in 195 towns and villages across Sierra Leone.1

All Data

Data is representative for 195 semi-rural towns across all Districts of Sierra Leone, with an average of 492 households per town. Rural villages and District headquarter towns are excluded.
